HEADWORD: Pichiciago
<hw>Pi`chi*ci*a"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small, burrowing, South American
edentate (<spn>Chlamyphorus truncatus</spn>), allied to the armadillos.
The shell is attached only along the back.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pichyciego</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pichurim bean</ent>⟦br⟧
